# Scalability [可扩展性] & High Availability

* scalability means that an application / system can handle greater loads by adapting
* there are two kinds of scalability :
    * vertical scalability
    * horizontal scalability (=elasticity)
* scalability is linked but different to high availability
## Scalability

### vertical scalability

* vertical scalability means increasing the size of the instance
* for example ,your application runs on a t2.micro
* scaling that application vertically means running it on a t2.large
* vertical scalability is very common for non distributed systems ,  such as a database
* RDS, ElastiCache are services that can scale vertically [RDS、ElastiCache 是可以垂直扩展的服务]
* there's usually a limit to how much you can vertically scale (hardware limit) [垂直扩展时有限的]
### horizontal scalability

* horizontal scalability means increasing the number of instances / systems for your application
* horizontal scaling implies distributed systems
* this is very common for web applications / modern applications
* it's easy to horizontally scale thanks the cloud offerings such as Amazon EC2
## High Availability

* high availability usually goes hand in hand with horizontal scaling
* high availability means running your application / system in at least 2 data centers (== availability zons)
* the goal of high availability is to survive a data center loss [高可用性的目标是在数据中心发生故障时仍能幸存] 
* the high availability can be passive [被动] (for RDS Multi AZ for example)
* this high availability can be active [主动] (for horizontal scaling)
# High Availability & Scalability For EC2

* Vertical Scaling : Increase instance size (= scale up/ down)
    * From :t2.nano - 0.5G of RAM,1vCPU
    * To : u-I 2tb1.mental -12.3TB of RAM, 448 vCPUs
* Horizontal Scaling: Increase number of instances (=scale out/in )
    * auto scaling group
    * load balancer [负载均衡]
* high availability : run instances for the same application across multi AZ
    * auto scaling group multi AZ
    * load balancer multi AZ
# Load Balancer

* load balancer are servers that forward [发送] traffic to multiple servers (e.g., EC2 instances) downstream [负载均衡器是将流量转发到下游多个服务器（例如 EC2 实例）的服务器]
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


## why use a load balancer ?

* spread [分散] load across multiple downstream instance [将负载分散到多个下游实例]
* expose [暴露] a single point of access (DNS) to your application [向您的应用程序公开单点访问 (DNS)]
* seamlessly [无缝地] handle failures of downstream instances [无缝处理下游实例的故障]
* do regular health checks to your instances
* provide SSL termination (HTTPS) for your websites
* enforce stickiness [粘性] with cookies [使用 cookie 增强粘性]
* high availability across zones [跨区域高可用性]
* separate public traffic from private traffic [将公共流量与私人流量分开]
## why use an Elastic Load Balancer ?

* an elastic load balancer is a managed load balancer [弹性负载均衡器是托管负载均衡器]
    * aws guarantees [保证] that is will be working
    * aws take care of   [负责] upgrades [升级], maintenance [维护], high availability
    * aws provides only a few configuration knobs [旋钮]
* it costs less to setup your own load balancer but it will be a lot more effort on your end
* it is integrated [集成] with many AWS offerings/services
    * EC2, EC2 Auto Scaling Groups,Amazon ECS
    * AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) ,CloudWatch
    * Route53,AWS WAF, AWS Global Accelerator [加速器]
## Health Checks

* health checks are crucial [至关重要的] for load balancers
* they enable the load balancer to know if instances it forwards [v. 发送] traffic to are available to reply to requests
* the health check is done on a port and a route (/health is common)
* if the response is not 200(OK), then the instance is unhealthy
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


## Types of load balancer on AWS

### AWS has 4 kinds of managed Load Balancers

* **Classic Load Balancer** (V1-old generation) -2009 -CLB
    * HTTP,HTTPS,TCP,SSL(secure TCP)
* **Application Load Balancer**(v2 - new generation) -2016-ALB
    * HTTP, HTTPS,Websocket
* **Network Load Balancer** (v2 - new generation) -2017 - NLB
    * TCP,TLS(secure TCP),UDP
* **Gateway Load Balancer** -2020 -GWLB
    * operations at layer 3(Newwork layer) - IP protocol
* overall, it is recommended [建议] to use the generation load balancers as they provide more features 
* some load balancers can be setup as internal [内部的](private) or external [外部的](public) ELBs

* **application security group : allow traffic only from load balancer**
### Application Load Balancer (v2)

* application load balancers is layer 7(HTTP)
* load balancing to multiple HTTP applications across machines [跨机器对多个 HTTP 应用程序进行负载平衡](target groups)
* load balancing to multiple applications on the same machine (ex : containers)
* support for HTTP/2 and websocket
* support redirects [重定向] (from http to https for example)
* Routing tables to different target groups:
    * routing based on path in URL(example.com**/users** & example.com**/posts**)
    * routing based on hostname in URL (**one.example.com** & **other.example.com**)
    * routing based on Query String ,Headers (example.com/users?**id=123&order=false**)
* ALB are a great fit for micro services & contain-based application(example: Docker & Amazon ECS)
* has a port mapping [映射] feature to redirect to a dynamic [动态] port in ECS
* in comparison [相比下], we'd need multiple Classic load balancer per application

### Network Load Balancer [works without cookies]

Network Load Balancer has one static IP address per AZ and you can attach an Elastic IP address to it. Application Load Balancers and Classic Load Balancers as a static DNS name.

* Network load balancers (Layer 4) allow to :
    * **Forward TCP & UDP traffic to your instances**
    * Handle million of request per seconds
    * Less latency ~ 100ms (vs 400ms for ALB)
* **NLB has****one static IP per AZ****, and supports assigning [分配] Elastic IP （**helpful for whitelisting specific IP **）**
* NLB are used for extreme performance ,TCP or UDP traffic
* not included in the AWS free tier

### Gateway Load Balancer

* Deploy ,scale and manage a fleet of 3rd party network virtual appliances in AWS [在 AWS 中部署、扩展和管理一组第三方网络虚拟设备]
* Example : firewalls ,intrusion detection [入侵检测] and prevention systems [预防系统], deep packet inspection systems [深度包检测系统],payload manipulation [有效负载操纵]...
* operation at layer 3(network layer) - IP packets [数据包]
* combines the following functions :
    * **Transparent [透明] Network Gateway** -- single entry / exit for all traffic
    * **Load Balancer**- distributes traffic to your virtual appliances [将流量分布到你的虚拟设备]
* Uses the **GENEVE**protocol on port **6081**

#### Target Groups

* **EC2 instances**
* **IP Address - must be private IPs**

## Sticky Sessions [粘性会话](Session Affinity)

ELB Sticky Session feature ensures traffic for the same client is always redirected to the same target (e.g., EC2 instance). This helps that the client does not lose his session data.

* it is possible to implement [实现] stickiness so that the same client is always redirected to the same instance behind a load balancer
* this works for **classic load balancer ,application load balancer ,and network load balancer.**
* the "cookie" used for stickiness has an expiration [过期] date you control
* use case : make sure the user doesn't lose his session date
* enabling stickiness may bring imbalance to the load over the backend EC2 instances [启用粘性可能会导致后端 EC2 实例的负载不平衡]
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


#### Cookie Names

* **application-based cookies**
    * custom cookie
        * generated by the target
        * can include any custom attributes [属性] required by the application
        * cookie name must be specified [指定] individually for each target group
        * don't use**AWSALB, AWSALBAPP, or AWSSLBTG**(reserved for use by the ELB [保留供 弹性负载均衡使用])
    * application cookie
        * generated by the load balancer
        * cookie name is **AWSALBAPP**
* **Duration-based Cookies [基于持续时间的cookie]**
    * cookie generated by the load balancer
    * cookie name is **ASWALB**for ALB,**AWSELB**for CLB
## Cross-Zone Load Balancing [跨区域负载均衡]

* each load balancer instance distributes evenly [均与地] across all registered instances in all AZ
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* Application load balancer
    * enabled by default (can be disabled at the target group level)
    * no charges for inter AZ data [可用区域之间不收费]
* Network load balancer & Gateway load balancer
    * disabled by default
    * you pay charges($) for inter AZ data if enabled
* Classic load balancer
    * disabled by default
    * no charges for inter AZ data if enabled
## SSL / TLS -Basics

* an SSL certificate allows traffic between your client and your load balancer to be encrypted in transit (in-flight encryption [飞行中加密])
* **SSL**refers to [指的是] Secure Sockets Layer [安全链路层] . used to encrypt connections
* **TLS**refers to Transport Layer [传输层] Security, which is a newer version
* nowadays,**TLS certificates are mainly used**, but people still refer as SSL
* public SSL certificate are issued by Certificate Authorities (CA) [公共 SSL 证书由证书颁发机构 (CA) 颁发]
* Comodo. Symantec.GoDaddy.GlobalSign,Digicert,Letsencrypt,etc......
* SSL certificates have an expiration [过期] date (you set) and must be renewed
### SSL certificates

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* the load balancer uses an X.509 certificate (SSL / TLS server certificate)
* you can manage certificate using ACM (AWS certificate manager)
* you can create upload your own certificates alternatively [也，或者]
* HTTPS listener :
    * you must specify a default certificate
    * you can add an optional list of certs [证书] to support multiple domains
    * **Clients can use SNI (server name indication [服务名称指示]) to specify the hostname they reach**
    * ability to specify a security policy to support older versions of SSL / TLS (legacy clients 旧客户端)
### *Server Name Indication (SNI)

* SNI solves the problem of loading multiple SSL certificates onto one web server (to serve multiple websites) [SNI 解决了将多个 SSL 证书加载到一台 Web 服务器上的问题（为多个网站提供服务）]
* it's a "newer" protocol ,and requires the client to **indicate [指明]**the hostname of the target server in the initial [最初的] SSL handshake
* the server will then find the correct certificate , or return the default onej
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


#### Note:

* only works for ALB & NLB (new generation), CloudFront
* does not work for CLB (old gen)
### Elastic Load Balancers - SSL Certificate

* **Classic Load Balancer (v1)**
    * support only one SSL certificate
    * must use multiple CLB for multiple hostname with multiple SSL certificatesddddd
* **Application Load Balancer (V2)**
    * supports multiple listeners with multiple SSL certificate
    * uses Server Name Indication (SNI) to make it work
* **Network Load Balancer (v2)**
    * supports multiple listeners with multiple SSL certificate
    * uses Server Name Indication (SNI) to make it work
# Connection Draining [连接耗尽]

*  Feature naming
    * connection draining [连接耗尽] - for CLB
    * deregistration delay [注销延迟]- for ALB & NLB
* time to complete "in-flight requests" while the instance is de-registering or unhealthy [当实例取消注册或运行状况不佳，它将为你的实例给予一些时间来完成正在进行的请求或活动的请求]
*  stop sending new requests to the EC2 instance which is de-registering
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* between 1 to 3600 seconds (default :300 seconds)
* can be disabled (set value to 0)
* set to a low value if your requests are short
# what's an Auto Scaling Group ?

* in real-life, the load on your website and application can change
* in the cloud, you can create  and get rid of servers very quickly
* the goal of an auto scaling group (ASG) is to :
    * scale out (add EC2 instances) to match an increased load
    * scale in (remove EC2 instances) to match an decreased load
    * ensure we have a minimum and a maximum number of EC2  instances running
    * automatically register new instance to a load instance
    * re-create an EC2 instance in case a previous one is terminated (ex:if unhealthy)
* ASG are free (you only pay for the underlying EC2 instances)

### auto scaling - cloudwatch alarm & scaling

* it's possible to scale an ASG based on CloudWatch alarms
* an alarm monitors a metric [警报监控指标] (such as**Average CPU**, or a **custom metric** [指标])
* metrics such as Average CPU are computed for the overall [整体，总]ASG instances 
* based on the alarm :
    * we can create scale-out policies (increase the number of instances)
    * we can create scale-in policies (decrease the number of instances)
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


## scaling policies

* **Dynamic Scaling**
    * **target tracking scaling**
        * simple to set-up
        * example : I want the average ASG CPU to stay at around 40%
    * **simple / step [步进] scaling**
        * when a cloudwatch alarm is triggered [触发](example CPU > 70%), then add 2 units
        * when a cloudwatch alarm is triggered (example CPU < 30%). then remove 1
* **Scheduled Scaling**
    * anticipate [预知] a scaling based on known usage patterns
    * example : increase the min capacity to 10 at 5 pm on Fridays
* **Predictive [预测] scaling**
    * continuously forecast [预测] load and schedule scaling ahead [提前]
### good metrics to scale on

* **CPUUtilization**: average CPU utilization [利用率] across your instances
* **RequestCountPerTarget**: to make sure the number of requests per EC2 instances is stable [稳定的].
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* **Average Network In / Out**(if you're application is network bound [绑定])
* **Any custom metric** (that you push using CloudWatch)
### Scaling Cooldowns [缩放冷却时间]

* after a scaling activity happens , you are in the**cooldown period (default 300 seconds)**
* during the cooldown period, the ASG will not launch or terminate additional instances (to allow for metrics to stabilize)
*  Advice: use a ready-to-use AMI to reduce configuration time in order to be serving request fasters and reduce the cooldown period
## Instance Refresh

* Goal : update launch template and then re-creating all EC2 instances
* for this we can use the native feature of instance refresh
* setting of minimum healthy percentage [百分比]
* specify warm-up [预热] time (how long until the instance is ready to use)
